THE SFA AMENDMENT
EXECUTION COPY
1
FIRST AMENDMENT TO ASSIGNMENT, CO-TENANCY, AND SHARED
FACILITIES AGREEMENT
This First Amendment to the Assignment, Co-Tenancy, and Shared Facilities Agreement
(this “Amendment”) is made and entered into by and among HECATE ENERGY HIGHLAND
LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Highland 1”), NEW MARKET SOLAR
PROJECTCO 1, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (f/k/a Hecate Energy Highland 2,
LLC, “New Market Solar 1”), NEW MARKET SOLAR PROJECTCO 2, LLC, a Delaware limited
liability company (f/k/a Hecate Energy Highland 4, LLC, “New Market Solar 2”), and
HIGHLAND SOLAR TRANSCO INTERCONNECTION LLC, a Delaware limited liability
company (“Transco”), to be effective on September 30, 2022. Highland 1, New Market Solar 1,
and New Market Solar 2 are sometimes referred to individually as a “Co-Tenant” or collectively
as the “Co-Tenants,” which terms shall include their permitted successors, assignees or nominees.
RECITALS
WHEREAS, the Co-Tenants entered into that certain Assignment, Co-Tenancy, and
Shared Facilities Agreement (the “Agreement”) on April 30, 2021, and Transco executed the
Agreement for the limited purpose of accepting and agreeing to the provisions of Section 2.8(g)
thereof.
WHEREAS, the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission accepted the Agreement by an
order issued on April 11, 2022, in FERC Docket No. ER22-1018-000.
WHEREAS, the Co-Tenants and Transco desire to amend the Agreement for the sole
purpose of confirming that the Agreement is consistent with that certain Interconnection Services
Agreement dated January 7, 2019, by and among PJM Interconnection, L.L.C., The Dayton Power
and Light Company, and Highland Solar Transco Interconnection LLC (“Transco”), as assignee
of Highland 1 (the “ISA”).
WHEREAS, the Co-Tenants and Transco agree that the reference to Section 2.8(g) of the
Agreement with respect to Transco’s execution of the Agreement should have been a reference to
Section 2.1(g).
NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants, representations
warranties, and agreements hereinafter set forth, and intended to be legally bound thereby, the CoTenants agree as follow:
1. The introductory paragraph of the SFA is revised to add the following sentence at the end
thereof:
“Highland Solar Transco Interconnection LLC, a Delaware limited liability company
(“Transco”), is executing this Agreement solely with respect to accepting and agreeing to
the provisions of Sections 2.1(g) and 2.1(h) hereof.”
2. Recital F is amended by replacing “Highland Solar Transco Interconnect LLC, a Delaware
limited liability company (“Transco”),” with “Transco”.
EXECUTION COPY
2
3. The Agreement is amended to add the following Section 2.1(h) thereto:
“(h) Each Co-Tenant hereby grants Transco the right to control such Co-Tenant’s
respective Phase or Phases upon completion of the construction of such Phase or
Phases for purposes of Transco complying with its obligations and exercising its
rights under the ISA. Each Co-Tenant specifically authorizes Transco to represent
and warrant to PJM that Transco will, upon completion of construction of each such
Phase, control such Phase. Each Co-Tenant agrees to take such actions as are
reasonably necessary for Transco to be able to (and to continue to be able to)
represent and warrant to PJM that it controls each Phase for which construction has
been completed.”
4. The following definition is added to Appendix A:
“Phase” means a portion of the “Customer Facility,” as such term is defined in the
ISA, for which construction has been completed. Together, the “Phases” shall
comprise the Customer Facility.
5. Capitalized terms not defined herein shall have the meanings give to them in the
Agreement.
6. Except as set forth in this Amendment, the remaining terms and conditions of the
Agreement remain in force.
[SIGNATURE PAGES FOLLOW]


EXECUTION COPY
5

effective as of the date first written above.
